                      Celebrating with a conscience                    The march for the search for the most caring and community-friendly pujas of Calcutta and Howrah started yesterday. In its eighth edition, CESC The Telegraph True Spirit Puja, partnered by Calcutta Police, West Bengal Fire Services, Calcutta Municipal Corporation, Pollution Control Board and The Bengal, has incorporated 271 pujas in its fold that are pledged to present people with a safe, happy and meaningful puja.                    Event: CESC The Telegraph True Spirit Puja When: Till October 15 Where: Across Calcutta and Howrah	                    
	drama      October 14 at Academy of Fine Arts; 3 pm: Pancham Vaidic presents its latest production, Tagores Ghare Baire, dramatised and directed by Arpita Ghosh.     October 14 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.45 pm: Arghya will stage Karna, directed by Manish Mitra.     October 15 at Academy of Fine Arts; 3 pm: The 102nd show of Helmet, a satiric play written by Rajat Ghosh and directed by Anish Ghosh. Produced by Shohan.     October 15 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Pratikriti presents Padma Nadir Majhi, directed by Alok Deb.     October 16 at Academy of Fine Arts; 3 pm amp; 6.30 pm: Nandikar presents Madhabi. Drama: Bhisma Sahni. Adaptation, music amp; direction: Swatilekha Sengupta. The cast includes Rudraprasad Sengupta, Debshankar Halder, Parthapratim Deb, Sumanta Ganguly and Sohini Sengupta.     October 16 at Tapan Theatre; 6.30 pm: Niva Arts presents Atmakatha. Direction amp; perfprmance: Soumitra Chattopadhyay.     October 18 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.45 pm: Rang Roop will stage Brojo Buror Sabuj Baksho, based on a story by Satyajit Ray. Direction: Seema Mukhopadhyay.     October 19 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Bratyajan presents Ruddha Sangeet, with Debshankar Halder in the role of legendary singer of Tagore songs, Debabrata Biswas. Drama amp; direction: Bratya Basu.     October 19 at Sisir Mancha; 6.30 pm: Ekti Dal presents Bidhuda, a comedy written and directed by Rajat Ghosh.     October 20 at Madhusudan Mancha; 6.30 pm: Gandhar will stage Kachher Manush, with Debshankar Halder and Bijoylakshmi Barman in the lead. Directed by filmmaker Gautam Haldar.     October 21 at Madhusudan Mancha; 6.30 pm: Belghoria Ethic will stage Kothay Pabo Tarey. Drama amp; direction: Debasis Sengupta.     
